Author: Jenny_Roberts
Text: My mom did zucchini boats one Thanksgiving!! She put zucchini halves in the oven, with parmesan on top and a little drizzle of oil. They were absolutely delicious!!  Also pumpkin/butternut soups, maybe try making your own cranberry jelly with sweetner instead and add orange zest and nutmeg etc :) or maybe find a version of low cal deviled eggs!

Author: toloache-dreams
Text: What I like to do for Thanksgiving as a side dish is a spicy roasted cauliflower dish, just cauliflower, salt, pepper, Italian herbs, red pepper flakes and a little bit of olive oil. Roast in the oven at 400 until the cauliflower is softened and crispy on the outside. I think it could work as an appetizer as well! It is always very popular with my family, one of the few things with no leftovers from what I've seen.
